FAQs
What is the average cost of study in Canada? The average cost ranges from CAD 15,000 to CAD 30,000 per year for tuition, with living expenses adding another CAD 10,000 to CAD 15,000 annually.

How long does it take to get a study permit? It typically takes several weeks to a few months to process a study permit, so it's advisable to apply well in advance.

Can international students work while studying? Yes, international students can work up to 20 hours per week during term time and full-time during breaks.

What are the best cities for international students in Canada? Cities like Toronto, Vancouver, and Montreal are popular among international students for their quality of education and vibrant lifestyle.

How can I apply for scholarships in Canada? Scholarships can be applied for through individual university websites and other scholarship portals. It's important to check the eligibility criteria and deadlines.
